<DOC><DOCNO> WSJ880202-0137 </DOCNO><HL> Who's News: John Wiley Names Ellis A Senior Vice President </HL><SO> </SO><CO> WNEWS WILLB </CO><DATELINE> NEW YORK  </DATELINE><TEXT>   Charles R. Ellis was named senior vice president, professional and trade publishing, of John Wiley andamp; Sons Inc.    Wiley is an international publisher of books, periodicals, software, databases and training materials for the professional and educational markets. Mr. Ellis, 52 years old, had been president and chief executive officer of Elsevier Science Publishing Co. in New York.    In addition, Serje G. Seminoff, 44, who has been vice president and general manager of Wiley's college division, was named senior vice president, educational publishing. </TEXT></DOC>